record_data.record_plain_text:
WestRock Virginia Corporation RATE SCHEDULE FOR WHOLESALE POWER SALES AT MARKET BASED RATES
1. Availability. WestRock Virginia Corporation ("Seller") may make sales of electric energy and capacity under this Rate Schedule to any entity that purchases power and energy for resale in any control area subject to the Commission's jurisdiction. 2. Applicability. This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Seller that are subject to the jurisdiction of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission") and are not made pursuant to a particular rate schedule on file with the Commission. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between purchaser and Seller. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions: Seller's market-based rate authority under this tariff is subject to the following waivers granted by the Commission by Order in MeadWestvaco Virginia Corp., Docket No. ER06-1419-001, at 2 (October 18, 2006) (unpublished letter order): waiver of Subparts B and C Part 35 of the Commission's regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; waiver of Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141 of the Commission's regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements with the exception of 18 C.F.R. 141.14 and 141.15; and blanket authorization under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations to issue securities and assume obligations or liabilities as guarantor, indorser, surety, or otherwise in respect of any security of another person; provided that such issue or assumption is for some lawful object within the corporate purposes of Seller, compatible with the public interest, and reasonably necessary or appropriate for such purposes.
Certain sales of energy, capacity and ancillary services by Seller are made pursuant to the Virginia State Corporation Commission's implementation of section 210 of PURPA, which, under 18 C.F.R. 292.601(c)(1), are exempt from Section 205 of the Federal Power Act. The Commission orders and certifications and re-certifications for Seller's QF status are as follows:
Westvaco Corp., QF83-45-001 (1982), QF83-45-001 (1989); MeadWestvaco Virginia Corp., QF83-45-002 (2002).
7. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller in all Commission-jurisdictional markets, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
8. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule is effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
